%% MLflow Operator - Data Flow Diagram
%% Generated by: Claude Opus 4.6

sequenceDiagram
    participant Admin as Platform Admin
    participant K8sAPI as Kubernetes API<br/>443/TCP HTTPS
    participant Operator as MLflow Operator<br/>(controller-manager)
    participant Helm as Helm Renderer<br/>(in-process)
    participant User as User Browser
    participant Gateway as data-science-gateway<br/>443/TCP HTTPS TLS 1.2+
    participant MLflow as MLflow Server<br/>8443/TCP HTTPS (service-ca)
    participant DB as Backend Store<br/>(PostgreSQL/MySQL)
    participant S3 as Artifact Storage<br/>(S3/GCS) 443/TCP HTTPS

    rect rgb(230, 245, 255)
        Note over Admin,Helm: Flow 1: MLflow CR Reconciliation
        Admin->>K8sAPI: Create MLflow CR<br/>(mlflow.opendatahub.io/v1)
        K8sAPI->>Operator: Watch event (TLS, SA Token)
        Operator->>Helm: Render chart with CR spec values<br/>(in-memory)
        Helm-->>Operator: Rendered K8s objects<br/>(Deployment, Service, SA, PVC, NetworkPolicy, RBAC)
        Operator->>K8sAPI: Server-Side Apply resources<br/>HTTPS/443, SA Token
        Operator->>K8sAPI: Create HTTPRoute (if Gateway API available)<br/>HTTPS/443, SA Token
        Operator->>K8sAPI: Create ConsoleLink (if OpenShift)<br/>HTTPS/443, SA Token
    end

    rect rgb(255, 245, 230)
        Note over User,S3: Flow 2: External User Access to MLflow UI
        User->>Gateway: GET /mlflow/*<br/>HTTPS/443, TLS 1.2+, Platform Auth
        Gateway->>MLflow: Forward to MLflow Service<br/>HTTPS/8443, TLS (service-ca)
        MLflow->>K8sAPI: SubjectAccessReview<br/>(user impersonation)<br/>HTTPS/443, SA Token
        K8sAPI-->>MLflow: Auth decision
        MLflow-->>Gateway: MLflow UI / API response
        Gateway-->>User: HTML/JSON Response
    end

    rect rgb(245, 255, 230)
        Note over User,S3: Flow 3: MLflow Client SDK Interaction
        participant Notebook as ML Workload<br/>(Notebook/Pipeline)
        Notebook->>Gateway: POST /mlflow/api/*<br/>HTTPS/443, Bearer Token
        Gateway->>MLflow: Rewrite to /api/*<br/>HTTPS/8443, TLS (service-ca)
        MLflow->>K8sAPI: SubjectAccessReview<br/>HTTPS/443
        K8sAPI-->>MLflow: Authorized
        MLflow->>DB: Store run metadata<br/>TCP, URI credentials
        DB-->>MLflow: Confirmation
        MLflow->>S3: Store artifacts<br/>HTTPS/443, Cloud credentials
        S3-->>MLflow: Confirmation
        MLflow-->>Gateway: API response
        Gateway-->>Notebook: JSON response
    end
